          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Energy resolution about 7 keV.",
                "Beam chopped for capture measurements so as to give",
                " 27 msec bursts separated by 53 msec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Capture was measured by detecting residual",
                "12B activity. The active region of the boron sample",
                "was defined in the vertical direction",
                " (i.e., perpendicular to the plane of the neutron and",
                "proton beams) by the edges of the scintillator and in",
                "the horizontal direction by a lead slit. The lead",
                "slit was curved so that the center line followed a",
                "constant neutron energy. Output pulses from the",
                "photomultiplier were amplified and then fed into a",
                "single-channel pulse-height analyzer, whose output",
                "was fed into a multichannel analyzer operating in the",
                "multiscaler mode with a time scale of 1 msec/channel.",
                "The start and stop of the counting by the",
                "multichannel analyzer was synchronized with the",
                "mechanical beam chopper so that the activity was",
                "measured between beam bursts. Runs were taken for a",
                "fixed number of monitor counts both with the boron",
                "sample in and with it out. The sample-out",
                "multichannel (time) spectra were subtracted from",
                "those taken with the sample in; the resultant (time)",
                "spectra were dominated by the B12 activity."
              ]
            }
          ],
